    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-10-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="449" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d449">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Bigelow</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 294.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-10-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 30, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 13th of October, No.
                            184, has been received. I thank you for the information you have given
                            me of the manner in which my No. 264 was received by Mr. Drouyn de
                            Lhuys, and I shall wait with interest for an account of the imperial
                            purposes in regard to the matter therein presented.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Bigelow,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
